name: Lost River Gorge (Visitor Center)
directions: Park, go over the little bridge and up the short trail toward the visitor center. This is the building where you buy tickets for the trails.  After entering the visitors center, the bathrooms will be in front of you to the left (to the left of the "staff only" door). The unisex bathroom is labeled "Family," and there are multi-stall "Men" and "Women" bathrooms nearby if you want them.
comment: The unisex bathroom is large and has a single toilet. The visitor center is a gift shop and also the place to buy tickets to the trail. The trail is great. Not 100% sure if the restroom is ADA accessible. The trails are generally not ADA accessible.
